018/**
019 * DTO for an HTML <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/edits.html#the-del-element">&lt;del&gt;</a>
020 * element.
021 *
022 * <p>
023 * The del element represents text that has been deleted from a document. It is typically rendered
024 * with a strikethrough effect to indicate that the content has been removed. The cite and datetime
025 * attributes can be used to provide information about when and why the deletion occurred.
026 *
027 * <h5 class='section'>Examples:</h5>
028 * <p class='bcode w800'>
029 *    <jk>import static</jk> org.apache.juneau.bean.html5.HtmlBuilder.*;
030 * 
031 *    <jc>// Simple deleted text</jc>
032 *    Del <jv>del1</jv> = <jsm>del</jsm>(<js>"This text has been removed."</js>);
033 * 
034 *    <jc>// Deleted text with citation and timestamp</jc>
035 *    Del <jv>del2</jv> = <jsm>del</jsm>()
036 *       .cite(<js>"https://example.com/revision-log"</js>)
037 *       .datetime(<js>"2024-01-15T10:30:00Z"</js>)
038 *       .text(<js>"Outdated information removed"</js>);
039 * 
040 *    <jc>// Deleted text with reason</jc>
041 *    Del <jv>del3</jv> = <jsm>del</jsm>()
042 *       .cite(<js>"https://example.com/corrections"</js>)
043 *       .datetime(<js>"2024-01-15"</js>)
044 *       .text(<js>"Incorrect statement"</js>)
045 *       .title(<js>"Removed due to factual error"</js>);
046 * </p>
047 *
048 * <p>
049 * The following convenience methods are provided for constructing instances of this bean:
050 * <ul class='javatree'>
051 *    <li class='jc'>{@link HtmlBuilder}
052 *    <ul class='javatree'>
053 *       <li class='jm'>{@link HtmlBuilder#del() del()}
054 *       <li class='jm'>{@link HtmlBuilder#del(Object, Object...) del(Object, Object...)}
055 *    </ul>
056 * </ul>
057 * </p>
058 *
059 * <h5 class='section'>See Also:</h5><ul>
060 *    <li class='link'><a class="doclink" href="https://juneau.apache.org/docs/topics/JuneauBeanHtml5">juneau-bean-html5</a>
061 * </ul>
062 */
063@Bean(typeName="del")
064@FluentSetters
065public class Del extends HtmlElementMixed {
066
067   /**
068    * Creates an empty {@link Del} element.
069    */
070   public Del() {}
071
072   /**
073    * Creates a {@link Del} element with the specified {@link Del#children(Object[])} node.
074    *
075    * @param children The {@link Del#children(Object[])} node.
076    */
077   public Del(Object...children) {
078      children(children);
079   }
080
081   /**
082    * <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/edits.html#attr-mod-cite">cite</a> attribute.
083    *
084    * <p>
085    * Specifies the URL of a document that explains the reason for the deletion.
086    * This provides context and justification for the edit.
087    *
088    * <p>
089    * The URL should point to a document that explains why the content was deleted.
090    *
091    * @param cite The URL explaining the reason for the deletion.
092    * @return This object.
093    */
094   public Del cite(String value) {
095      attr("cite", value);
096      return this;
097   }
098
099   /**
100    * <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/edits.html#attr-mod-datetime">datetime</a> attribute.
101    *
102    * <p>
103    * Specifies the date and time when the content was deleted. Used for tracking
104    * the history of document changes.
105    *
106    * <p>
107    * The value should be a valid date-time string in ISO 8601 format.
108    *
109    * @param datetime The date and time when the content was deleted.
110    * @return This object.
111    */
112   public Del datetime(String value) {
113      attr("datetime", value);
114      return this;
115   }
